# Vue Component Architecture Rules

All components must follow **Vue 3 Composition API with TypeScript**.

Use `<script setup lang="ts">`.

---

## Standard Component Structure

Every component must follow this structure:

<script setup lang="ts">

// imports
import { computed } from "vue"

// props
interface Props {
  label?: string
}

const props = defineProps<Props>()

</script>

<template>

</template>

<style scoped>
</style>

---

## Component Responsibilities

Components should be:

- reusable
- small
- single-responsibility

Avoid components larger than **150–200 lines**.

If a component grows too large:

Split into smaller components inside `/components`.

---

## Naming Conventions

Component files must use **PascalCase**.

Examples:

Button.vue
UserAvatar.vue
DashboardCard.vue
FormInput.vue

Usage:

<Button />
<UserAvatar />

---

## Component Categories

Structure components into logical folders if the library grows.

Example:

/components
  /ui
    Button.vue
    Input.vue
    Modal.vue
    Card.vue

  /form
    FormField.vue
    FormInput.vue

  /layout
    PageContainer.vue
    AppHeader.vue

---

## Props Rules

All props must be typed.

Example:

interface Props {
  label: string
  disabled?: boolean
}

---

## Emitting Events

Use typed emits.

Example:

const emit = defineEmits<{
  (e: "submit"): void
}>()

---

## Logic Separation

If logic becomes complex:

Move it to:

/composables

Example:

/composables/useForm.ts

Components should focus primarily on **UI rendering**.

The styling should not be overridable by the importer of the component. Any new requirement of customisation should be provided at the lower level component. e.g if a button is needed in 3 sizes, then the props from the parent can be props.size: 'base' | 'small' | 'large' | 'xlarge'. the parent should not pass explicit padding and margin styles to change the size of the button. this is to avoid the importer specifying different styles at different places in the app leading to inconsistent visual everywhere.

Whenever a button needs to show the loading state. always use the loading variant instead of manually hardcoding the disabled and loading text.